============================================================
03 – BIG 5 MATCHUP ANALYSIS (04_03.csv)
============================================================

Description:
This section focuses on head-to-head matchups between the
top Premier League teams: Arsenal, Manchester City,
Manchester United, Chelsea, and Liverpool.

The goal is to analyze how these teams perform against each
other in terms of scoring, competitiveness, and match
intensity.

Unlike previous sections that analyze teams individually,
this section highlights direct interactions between elite
teams, providing insights into rivalry dynamics and match
behavior.


------------------------------------------------------------
Diagrams & Analysis
------------------------------------------------------------


1. Big 5 Matchups - Average Goals (big5_avg_goals.png)

Description:
This chart ranks matchups based on the average number of
goals scored.

Comment:
Arsenal vs Liverpool stands out as the highest scoring
matchup, followed by Liverpool vs Manchester City. These
games tend to be open and attacking, indicating strong
offensive play from both sides.


------------------------------------------------------------


2. Big 5 Matchups - Intensity Score (big5_intensity_score.png)

Description:
Measures match intensity using fouls, yellow cards, and
red cards.

Comment:
Chelsea vs Manchester United and Arsenal vs Manchester United
appear as the most intense matchups, suggesting more physical
and competitive games. These fixtures tend to involve more
aggressive play.


------------------------------------------------------------


3. Big 5 Matchups - Win Dominance (big5_dominance.png)

Description:
Shows the difference in win rates between the two teams in
each matchup.

Comment:
Arsenal vs Manchester City shows the highest dominance,
indicating a clear advantage for one side. On the other hand,
Liverpool vs Manchester City appears highly balanced, with
almost equal performance between the teams.


------------------------------------------------------------


4. Big 5 Matchup Performance Overview (big5_matchup_heatmap.png)

Description:
Heatmap comparing key performance metrics for each matchup,
including:
- average goals
- fouls
- shots
- corners

Comment:
This visualization provides a complete view of each matchup’s
playing style. For example, Arsenal vs Liverpool combines high
scoring with high attacking activity (shots and corners),
while Chelsea vs Manchester United shows high intensity with
increased fouls.

It allows quick comparison between matchups in terms of both
offensive behavior and physicality.


------------------------------------------------------------
Summary
------------------------------------------------------------

This section highlights how top teams interact with each
other, revealing patterns in scoring, competitiveness, and
match intensity.

It shows that:
- some matchups are consistently high-scoring and attacking
- others are more physical and defensive
- certain rivalries are balanced, while others are clearly
  dominated by one team

These insights provide a deeper understanding of elite-level
football dynamics and complement the team-level analysis
from the previous section.